      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The common failure mode for vector-only RAG is queries containing rare tokens: product codes, error messages, proper names, or version numbers. BM25 handles these exactly. The common failure mode for BM25-only is paraphrasing and intent: the user says \"slow\" but the document says \"latency\". Hybrid catches both."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Reciprocal Rank Fusion (RRF)"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "RRF is the simplest and most robust fusion method. It converts both result lists into rank positions, then scores each document with "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "1 / (k + rank)"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " where "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "k"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " is a smoothing constant (default 60). A document appearing at rank 1 in BM25 and rank 3 in vector search gets a higher combined score than one appearing at rank 5 in both. RRF requires no score normalisation — it only uses rank positions, making it robust to different score scales between retrieval systems."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "def reciprocal_rank_fusion(\n    bm25_results: list[tuple[str, float]],   # [(doc_id, score), ...]\n    vector_results: list[tuple[str, float]],\n    k: int = 60,\n) -> list[tuple[str, float]]:\n    \"\"\"\n    Fuse two ranked lists using RRF.\n    Returns [(doc_id, rrf_score)] sorted by score descending.\n    \"\"\"\n    scores: dict[str, float] = {}\n\n    for rank, (doc_id, _) in enumerate(bm25_results, start=1):\n        scores[doc_id] = scores.get(doc_id, 0.0) + 1.0 / (k + rank)\n\n    for rank, (doc_id, _) in enumerate(vector_results, start=1):\n        scores[doc_id] = scores.get(doc_id, 0.0) + 1.0 / (k + rank)\n\n    return sorted(scores.items(), key=lambda x: x[1], reverse=True)\n\n\n# Example usage\nbm25_hits   = [(\"doc3\", 0.82), (\"doc1\", 0.71), (\"doc7\", 0.54)]\nvector_hits = [(\"doc1\", 0.91), (\"doc5\", 0.78), (\"doc3\", 0.62)]\n\nfused = reciprocal_rank_fusion(bm25_hits, vector_hits)\n# [('doc1', 0.0328), ('doc3', 0.0313), ('doc5', 0.0161), ('doc7', 0.0154)]"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Linear Score Fusion (Alpha Weighting)"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "When you want explicit control over the contribution of each retriever, normalise both score lists to [0, 1] and blend them with an "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "alpha"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " parameter: "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "final = alpha * vector_score + (1 - alpha) * bm25_score"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ". "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "alpha = 1.0"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " is pure vector; "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "alpha = 0.0"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " is pure BM25. Start at 0.5 and tune on a labelled evaluation set."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "def normalise(scores: list[tuple[str, float]]) -> dict[str, float]:\n    \"\"\"Min-max normalise scores to [0, 1].\"\"\"\n    if not scores:\n        return {}\n    values = [s for _, s in scores]\n    lo, hi = min(values), max(values)\n    if hi == lo:\n        return {doc_id: 1.0 for doc_id, _ in scores}\n    return {doc_id: (s - lo) / (hi - lo) for doc_id, s in scores}\n\n\ndef linear_fusion(\n    bm25_results: list[tuple[str, float]],\n    vector_results: list[tuple[str, float]],\n    alpha: float = 0.5,\n) -> list[tuple[str, float]]:\n    \"\"\"\n    alpha=1.0 -> pure vector; alpha=0.0 -> pure BM25.\n    \"\"\"\n    bm25_norm   = normalise(bm25_results)\n    vector_norm = normalise(vector_results)\n\n    all_ids = set(bm25_norm) | set(vector_norm)\n    fused = {\n        doc_id: alpha * vector_norm.get(doc_id, 0.0)\n                + (1 - alpha) * bm25_norm.get(doc_id, 0.0)\n        for doc_id in all_ids\n    }\n    return sorted(fused.items(), key=lambda x: x[1], reverse=True)"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Implementing Hybrid Search in PostgreSQL"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "PostgreSQL provides "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "ts_vector"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " / "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "ts_query"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " for BM25-style full-text search and pgvector's "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "<=>"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " for vector similarity. You can run both in a single query using a CTE and merge ranks in SQL."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "sql"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "-- Add both search columns to your chunks table\nALTER TABLE document_chunks\n    ADD COLUMN fts tsvector\n        GENERATED ALWAYS AS (to_tsvector('english', chunk_text)) STORED;\n\nCREATE INDEX ON document_chunks USING GIN (fts);\nCREATE INDEX ON document_chunks USING hnsw (embedding vector_cosine_ops);\n\n-- Hybrid query: RRF fusion in pure SQL\nWITH bm25 AS (\n    SELECT id, chunk_text,\n           ROW_NUMBER() OVER (ORDER BY ts_rank(fts, query) DESC) AS bm25_rank\n    FROM   document_chunks,\n           plainto_tsquery('english', $1) AS query\n    WHERE  fts @@ query\n    LIMIT  50\n),\nvec AS (\n    SELECT id, chunk_text,\n           ROW_NUMBER() OVER (ORDER BY embedding <=> $2::vector) AS vec_rank\n    FROM   document_chunks\n    ORDER  BY embedding <=> $2::vector\n    LIMIT  50\n),\nfused AS (\n    SELECT\n        COALESCE(b.id, v.id)          AS id,\n        COALESCE(b.chunk_text, v.chunk_text) AS chunk_text,\n        COALESCE(1.0 / (60 + b.bm25_rank), 0)\n            + COALESCE(1.0 / (60 + v.vec_rank), 0) AS rrf_score\n    FROM  bm25 b FULL OUTER JOIN vec v ON b.id = v.id\n)\nSELECT id, chunk_text, rrf_score\nFROM   fused\nORDER  BY rrf_score DESC\nLIMIT  $3;"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "import psycopg2\n\ndef hybrid_search_pg(\n    conn,\n    query_text: str,\n    query_embedding: list[float],\n    top_k: int = 5,\n) -> list[dict]:\n    with conn.cursor() as cur:\n        cur.execute(\n            \"\"\"\n            WITH bm25 AS (\n                SELECT id, chunk_text,\n                       ROW_NUMBER() OVER (ORDER BY ts_rank(fts, q) DESC) AS bm25_rank\n                FROM document_chunks, plainto_tsquery('english', %s) AS q\n                WHERE fts @@ q\n                LIMIT 50\n            ),\n            vec AS (\n                SELECT id, chunk_text,\n                       ROW_NUMBER() OVER (ORDER BY embedding <=> %s::vector) AS vec_rank\n                FROM document_chunks\n                ORDER BY embedding <=> %s::vector\n                LIMIT 50\n            ),\n            fused AS (\n                SELECT\n                    COALESCE(b.id, v.id) AS id,\n                    COALESCE(b.chunk_text, v.chunk_text) AS chunk_text,\n                    COALESCE(1.0/(60+b.bm25_rank),0)+COALESCE(1.0/(60+v.vec_rank),0) AS score\n                FROM bm25 b FULL OUTER JOIN vec v ON b.id = v.id\n            )\n            SELECT id, chunk_text, score FROM fused ORDER BY score DESC LIMIT %s\n            \"\"\",\n            (query_text, query_embedding, query_embedding, top_k),\n        )\n        return [\n            {\"id\": row[0], \"text\": row[1], \"score\": float(row[2])}\n            for row in cur.fetchall()\n        ]"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Hybrid Search with Weaviate"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Weaviate exposes hybrid search natively. Set "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "alpha"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " in the query — it uses BM25 internally for the keyword side and the collection's vectorizer for the semantic side, then fuses with its own RRF implementation."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "import weaviate\n\nclient = weaviate.connect_to_weaviate_cloud(\n    cluster_url=\"https://my-cluster.weaviate.network\",\n    auth_credentials=weaviate.auth.AuthApiKey(\"your-key\"),\n)\n\ndef hybrid_search_weaviate(\n    query_text: str,\n    query_vector: list[float],\n    alpha: float = 0.5,\n    limit: int = 5,\n) -> list[dict]:\n    collection = client.collections.get(\"DocumentChunk\")\n    result = collection.query.hybrid(\n        query=query_text,       # BM25 term\n        vector=query_vector,    # semantic embedding\n        alpha=alpha,            # 0=BM25 only, 1=vector only, 0.5=equal\n        limit=limit,\n        return_properties=[\"chunk_text\", \"source\", \"page\"],\n        return_metadata=[\"score\"],\n    )\n    return [\n        {\n            \"text\": obj.properties[\"chunk_text\"],\n            \"source\": obj.properties[\"source\"],\n            \"score\": obj.metadata.score,\n        }\n        for obj in result.objects\n    ]"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Connecting Hybrid Search to Claude"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "import anthropic\n\nclaude = anthropic.Anthropic()\n\ndef rag_with_hybrid(\n    conn,\n    query: str,\n    query_embedding: list[float],\n) -> str:\n    chunks = hybrid_search_pg(conn, query, query_embedding, top_k=6)\n    if not chunks:\n        return \"No relevant documents found.\"\n\n    context = \"\\n\\n---\\n\\n\".join(\n        f\"[{i+1}] {c['text']}\" for i, c in enumerate(chunks)\n    )\n\n    response = claude.messages.create(\n        model=\"claude-opus-4-8\",\n        max_tokens=1024,\n        system=\"Answer the question using only the provided context. Cite source numbers like [1].\",\n        messages=[{\n            \"role\": \"user\",\n            \"content\": f\"Context:\\n{context}\\n\\nQuestion: {query}\",\n        }],\n    )\n    return response.content[0].text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Tuning Alpha and k"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "Start with RRF (k=60): "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "It requires no per-query normalisation and is robust to mismatched score scales between retrievers. Use it as a baseline."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "Move to linear alpha when: "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "you have a labelled evaluation set (query, relevant docs) and want to optimise retrieval metrics (NDCG@10, MRR). Grid-search alpha in [0.1, 0.3, 0.5, 0.7, 0.9]."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "Query-adaptive alpha: "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Short queries (1-2 tokens) with technical terms benefit from lower alpha (more BM25). Long natural-language queries benefit from higher alpha (more semantic). Route by query length or use a classifier."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "Candidate pool size: "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Fetch top-50 from each retriever before fusion, then return top-5 to Claude. A narrow BM25 pool misses documents that only score well after fusion."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "Re-ranking: "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "For high-stakes RAG, add a cross-encoder re-ranker (e.g. Cohere Rerank) after hybrid fusion. Cross-encoders are slower but consider query-document interaction jointly."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Common Mistakes"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "Fusing scores directly without normalisation: "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "BM25 scores are unbounded; cosine similarity is [−1, 1]. Linear fusion without normalisation means BM25 always dominates. Either normalise or use RRF."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "Using the same top-k for fusion input as output: "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "If you fetch top-5 from BM25 and top-5 from vector, a document at rank 6 in BM25 but rank 1 in vector is invisible to the fusion. Fetch top-50 before fusing, output top-5."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "Forgetting to update FTS index on chunk updates: "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "PostgreSQL's generated "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "code"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "tsvector"
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " column updates automatically on INSERT/UPDATE, but if you bulk-load via COPY, run "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "code"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "UPDATE document_chunks SET fts = to_tsvector('english', chunk_text)"
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " afterward."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "Not measuring retrieval quality: "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Without an evaluation dataset, you cannot know if hybrid improves over pure vector for your data. Build a small labelled set (50-100 queries) early and track NDCG."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Summary"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Hybrid search combines BM25 keyword retrieval and vector semantic retrieval through score fusion, most simply via Reciprocal Rank Fusion. It outperforms either approach alone on diverse query types: BM25 handles exact terms and rare tokens while vector search handles paraphrase and intent. In PostgreSQL, a CTE with "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "ts_rank"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " and "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "<=>"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " implements hybrid search with no additional dependencies. In Weaviate, "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "collection.query.hybrid()"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " handles fusion automatically. Start with "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "alpha=0.5"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " and RRF fusion, measure retrieval quality on a labelled set, then tune from there."
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  }
}